  "prompt": "How do I get Jimmy Wales to answer my question on Quora?",
  "response": "Getting a prominent figure like Jimmy Wales to answer your question on Quora can be challenging, but here are some strategies you can try:\n\n1. **Ask Insightful Questions**: Make sure your question is thoughtful and relevant to his expertise or interests. Consider what topics he is passionate about or has previously discussed.\n\n2. **Tag the Right Topics**: Use appropriate tags to categorize your question. This makes it easier for him and others interested in those topics to find your question.\n\n3. **Engage with His Content**: Follow him on Quora and engage with his posts. Commenting thoughtfully on his answers might increase the chances of him noticing you.\n\n4. **Use Direct Mentions**: If you ask your question directly and tag him (if Quora's interface allows), he may be more inclined to respond.\n\n5. **Be Patient and Respectful**: Understand that high-profile individuals receive many questions. Even if you don\u2019t get an answer, approach the situation with patience and respect.\n\n6. **Be Specific**: A well-defined, specific question will be more likely to attract attention than a vague one.\n\nRemember that there's no guaranteed way to get a specific response, but these tips can improve your chances!",
